hooks.prompt:
Review whether this conversation involved producing a plan, proposal, or implementation approach â€” meaning any proposal for how code will be structured, what guarantees will hold, or how correctness will be maintained.

Simple code edits that don't involve architectural or correctness decisions (e.g., fixing a typo, adding a log line, renaming a variable) do NOT count as plans.

If a plan or implementation approach was produced:
- Check whether the fanatic subagent (from .claude/agents/fanatic.md) was invoked during this conversation
- Check whether the fanatic returned an APPROVED verdict
- If the fanatic was NOT invoked, or was invoked but did NOT return APPROVED, return: {"decision": "block", "reason": "Plan must be reviewed and approved by the fanatic subagent before completing"}
- If the fanatic was invoked AND returned APPROVED, return: {"decision": "approve"}

If NO plan or implementation approach was produced (just a question/answer, a simple code edit, research, etc.), return: {"decision": "approve"}
